review: while the chips are great their ingredients list is deceptive note the wording for the oil though the first oil listed canola is expeller pressed theexpeller pressed only applies as worded to the canola oil thats how english grammer works if they wanted expeller pressed to apply to all the oils at least according to the fda it must be specified for each oil separately which is not done and the product may not actually contain any canola oil since expeller pressed oils are more expensive than chemically processed oils which comprise that vast bulk of oils sold in the us the consumer has to assume that the sunflower and safflower oil are chemically processed and since chemically processed sunflower oil is the cheapest among the three thats probably what is used and comprises the bulk of the oil usedi would love for garden of eatin to respond but am guessing they wont they know what they meant to do deceive those customers that are buying these chips because of the expeller pressed canola oilwhich probably makes up a tiny porition of the oil used if any

review: let me start by saying these bad boys are worth every penny and prove that not all washes are created equal i feel as though i have conducted my own experiments with my tide free and gentle pods my test subject was mainly my husband who is a diesel mechanic needless to say a month ago our laundry care products consisted of every stain fighter on the market  dawn dish soap we even have dawn in our shower because hes always covered in various oils especially motor oil now i am not going to lie the first couple times i used these it was only on our whites  and from the actual difference i seen from the moment i pulled our whites out of the dryer was just amazing i mean my used to be dingy white sports bras looked brand new again but i was still skeptical on how effective this product would be on his oil covered clothes so i had stuck to our harsh chemical filled dawn routine  until yesterday  i finally figured hey its at least worth a couple pods to see if it will help especially after it cleaned up our whites so wellso i loaded up the washing machine with his work pants shirts and even a pair of my shorts that i had somehow gotten soot on yes we have come to realize that we arent pristine people lol anyways when i pulled the darks from the dryer and checked over the shorts and where the soot had been i was doing my happy dance  this stuff has saved our wardrobe and in the long run  and yet we are astounded that something can be both mighty and gentle in the absolute perfect way we just love my tide free and gentle pods that i received freefromtide and buzzagent knowing everything this stuff has done and all the while without harsh chemicals and dyes i am simply grateful for being able to try these and give these out so others can see how amazing these things arejust remember do not handle with wet hands lol other than that load your clothes one or two of these and your good to gothanks again buzzagent and tide for giving me a second skin care routine that is so powerful and healthy
product: tide pods free amp gentle he turbo laundry detergent pacs  count tub packaging may vary

review: this stuff works excellent we had a horrible roach problem after my husbands friend moved in with us from out of state unfortunately he transferred his pest into our home we tried bug bombs sprays sticky pads boric acid etc while some products kept them away it was only temporary and we battled roaches on and off for  yrs one issue was our neighbors had a roach problem and everytime they treated their home they would travel back into ours my sister in law lived in military housing where she battled roaches at one time she mentioned this gel saying its the best shes ever used when all else failed the combat gel worked after putting this in all corners cracks window seals behind appliances etc within days we noticed the roaches were slow moving and mostly dead it took roughly two weeks and we were free of roaches up until about  yrs ago i was still adding a little of the gel here and there just for prevention while we havent had roaches in years recently we started getting palmetto bugs  wood roaches  those two inch sometimes flying roaches i live down south and apparently theyre common for everyone i never had much of an issue with them killing the one or two id see a year this past year however i been killing maybe  a week and it hadnt occurred to me that possibly using the combat gel is why i had rarely seen them so a cpl of days ago i hunted out my gel and hit up all my windows door cracks and even put little drops underneath our vent covers since apparently they can get in through the duct work of our heating and air unit now were just waiting and hoping it keeps the palmettos out like it did the other roaches

review: i started feeding both of my dogs purina one smartblend lamb  rice about two months ago and the last two or three weeks they have both been vomiting almost all of their food undigested about  hours after eating i looked for many causes thinking especially that they were eating too fast and tried different feeding methods to help slow them down but it only got worse my cavalier was vomiting violently all day yesterday and last night my lab started vomiting blood we are now sure it was the food and when i did some research last night i found out purina has pending lawsuits from a fairly large group of consumers who claim their dogs were poisoned by the food and had all the same symptoms my dogs are having this morning i fed both dogs small amounts of a new food and a little more of the new food this afternoon and for the first time in weeks theyve both held everything down and both already look and seem a lot better i just hope we stopped feeding them the purina in time and there are no long term health issueswhat makes me the most upset is when i contacted purina over the phone they denied any issues with their products and removed my post describing my experience from their facebook page because it did not adhere to community standards in the last few months there are over  incidents listed on consumer affairs site almost identical to my experience some worse yet purina stands by the safety of their products and feels these reports are all false and misleading allegations i am not one to ever complain to a corporation  usually if im unhappy with a product i just throw it away and move on  but this is extremely frightening and purina needs to take this seriously
product: purina one dog smartblend lamb amp rice formula adult  lb packaging may vary

review: if youre looking for something to freshen up the smell of your carpet than this is an excellent choice initially i began my search for a carpet deodorizer after a sweet potato i had been storing under my bed had gone south and leaked all its potato juices all over my carpet yes i know i shouldnt have been storing it under my bed its a small shared apartment and i didnt want my roommates to take it dont judge  the smell wasnt terrible but no matter what i tried i couldnt get it out i used multiple carpet cleaners and sprays over multiple weeks which cleaned up the stain but the smell was still there arm  hammer was the only product i found that got the smell out and after only one use i never thought that potato smell would leave so i imagine that itll work on just about any smellthere are multiple scents of this brand although this is the most common ive seen and probably the best smelling the powder is very potent and the scent is very strong for the first day and then is more like a background smell for the next two weeks or so you get the best effect if you follow the instructions and sprinkle it generously on the carpet and let it sit for  minutes before vacuuming it up i have a pretty small room so i use about half the box each time but the smell last for about a month as a bonus if you have a vacuum with a bag it keeps your vacuuming smelling fresh for multiple months its been about  months since i last used the product in my room but my i can smell it on my vacuum every time i take it out of the closettip this packaging does tend to leak a little bit of powder when handling even when you get it at the store the box in my pantry package did leak a little and ive contacted amazon about putting a bag and more protected around this particular product  but amazon is great and will refund you if you get a damaged product so i wouldnt stress too much about it
product: arm amp hammer extra strength carpet odor eliminator  oz

review: in the past ive made my own dry rubs that were delicious on pork chicken and steak  however in a time pinch a couple of years ago i picked up a container of this mccormick grill mates dry rub for steaks at the grocery at the same time that i picked up the steaks  and ive been sold on it ever sincewhile i usually grill our steaks outside during the summer months my favorite method of steak preparation is with a cast iron skillet that has been preheated in a  degree oven  i brush or rub a very thin coat of canola oil on both sides of thickcut tenderloins or other steak cuts and then spoon an even coating of the dry rub over both sides of the steaks and allow them to set at room temperature for  minutes  remove the skillet careful its very hot from the oven and immediately place over high heat on the stovetop  place the steaks in the hot skillet and they will sear immediately  i turn the steaks over after several minutes and allow the other side to get a seared crust also another  minutes  then place the skillet back into the  degree oven until the steaks reach degree of preferred doneness  the time in the oven depends on the thickness of the steaks and the degree of doneness required usually  minutes  our family prefers our steaks done mediumrare so this method takes very little time on both stovetop and in oven  this cast iron skillet method in addition to using this dry rub gives the steaks a bold flavorful crispyseared crust on both sides but retains all of the juices insidethe ingredients of this dry rub are garlic spices and herbs including black pepper salt brown sugar onion paprika silicon dioxide added to make free flowing sunflower oil and spice extractives

review: lets be clear buying supplements online even on amazon is a big pain largely because of the industrys saturation with unethical companies selling snake oil who use shills to pad the  star reviews and give products that dont work a misleadingly high review rating so understand that i am in no way affiliated with this company or any of its employees i have not been paid or provided any free products in exchange for my review i said all that just so say this zinc picolinate has changed my life i have suffered from severe anxiety and premenstrual disorder for my entire life  i had postpartum depression that destroyed my marriage all my life i was put on antidepressants antianxiety meds adhd meds etc all the while i knew i showed all the signs of elevated copper levels i had been doing research but since the medical community never really addressed it i kept it on the back burner one day i started researching how to combat elevated copper levels zinc was the answer but not all zinc supplements are created equal because some arent readily absorbed in the body so i further researched and found picolinate is the most absorbable form i happened to choose this brand no particular reason like i said it changed my life im also doing magnesium citrate the kind that comes in powdered form that you mix with liquid im shocked that all these years there was a way i could actually live life without feeling perpetually stressed and riddled with anxiety ive only been taking it for a couple of weeks but the change has been pronounced im not sure what it will do to my copper levels in the long term i may end up needing a supplement that balances them but just decreasing the effects of copper on my hormones and brain chemistry has been lifechanging

review: these are my absolute favorite diapers since my son was born feb  and will continue to be my first choice with my second due march  recent reviews have been negative though so i wanted to say a few thingsthese diapers hold a lot but you need to check your kids and make sure they arent filling it every diaper has a limit and its your job as a parent to check and change frequently if there are crystals leaking out of the diaper that is a user error not a manufacturing defect the crystals will only leak out if the diaper has been filled to the max and allowed to sit for some timeblow outs and leaking if it blows out the top you either need to put the diaper on tighter or move up a size the side straps will stretch and become loose as your child wears the diaper so although it may look uncomfortably tight on your child it will stretch out and keep you from having out the too blow outs i recommend stretching the side straps out as you are sticking them in place so that they wont have too much stretching leeway and result in a blow out or the diaper falling down you also need to put the straps on straight across angling them makes the diaper distort and can result in a leakif the diaper is leaking out the legs make sure to always tuck the diaper in around babys leg folds and not on the thigh this will minimize so many leaks of all kindsthese are great diapers just dont get sloppy and they will work tight waist remember the straps stretch tuck the legs in around the babys thigh rolls keep it higher in the back than the front if they consistently shoot up the back it might be time to move up a size and crystals will only leak if you arent changing the baby as often as you should

review: most of my childhood was spent in want of quality catsup served in an easy to pour device  as hard as i have tried to forget so many tormented images still seem to surface from time to time  like the time that i found my memaw dead on the kitchen floor clutching a clogged bottle of kirks economy catsup  i dont care what the police say with their whole gampy stabbed memaw theory  fact is cheap catsup played a role in this horrible event an event that could have easily been avoided if only memaw had access to heinz tomato ketchup  easy squeeze bottlesand its not just the death of my dear memaw  the ugly head of sub quality catsup reared its head again during what should have been those wonderful early teen years everyone talks about  it was early summer and gampy had just been released early from the warren county correctional facility for good behavior  we were all gathered for a summer picnic gampys out of prison celebration well everyone except for memaw although she was there in spirit  all was going along swimmingly until my pops delivered a plate of beautifully grilled hotdogs and burgers to the table  as a gesture of welcome home gampy i leaned forward and grabbed the cumbersome glass bottle of cheap connys country catsup and proceeded to apply it to gampys dog  when i awoke in the hospital  weeks later i was brought up to speed on the series of events that followed my attempt to use a lesser quality catsup  events that my brain surgeon informed me i may never recover  to quickly summarize years of cheap homemade prison toilet catsup had left a brutal impression on gampy  when my hair is cut very short you can still see this impression on the back of my skullit was not until i hit my late  that an event finally sent me over the edge and i had the epiphany concerning crappy catsup and its dire effects on the human condition  as a handsome young  year old buck you can imagine i had my pick of the ladies  and did i ever pick a good one  roberta was as pretty as she was smart and boy was she smart  she was finishing her phd in physics captain of her schools debate team and a champion chess player in warren county  seems like there wasnt anything roberta did wrong  well with the exception of her constant purchasing of mid grade catsup dispensed through inefficient containers  it was just a mere  years prior to the release of heinz tomato ketchup  easy squeeze bottles  a fact that just haunts me  due to severe heart problems gampy had been released once again from the warren county correctional facility  he was living with me temporarily while pops try to find a home for him  i was working late and roberta had called me and let me know that she was making dinner for her a gampy and that she would try and save some french fries for me  damn those french fries and their dependece upon tastey catsup served convientlythe squad cars were in the driveway when i got home that night  we will never really be sure what happened that night  what we do know is that gampy and roberta are in a better place now  a heavenly place that is not burdened by watered down catsup that tastes like chemical tomatoesi swore that night that i would never consume catsup again  and then one day i stumbled across heinz tomato ketchup  easy squeeze bottles  it was pure heaven served easily through a squeeze bottle  since using heinz tomato ketchup  easy squeeze bottles my life has been for the better  my only regret is that my dear gamby had to pass so soon and miss this wonderful product
product: heinz tomato ketchup  oz value size bottle

for rating this product as i have and will thereby consider my review unhelpful but so be it  i have principles that i must remain true to  here is why i downgraded the rating from five to three doesnt  by trying to quash efforts to pass laws requiring gmolabeling and in many cases attempting to reverse the laws that some states have recently passed requiring gmo labeling blue diamond is review: i feel as if it would not be a complete review if i did not tell my history of having roaches these little demons have been in most houses ive lived in my entire life because my parents dont care about getting rid of them and that is something that everyone in the house needs to be a part of or at least aware of they were something that i thought was a plague on my life i literally never went a year without seeing them everywhere in my lifetime i have tried probably every spray and bug bomb on the general market nothing ever worked the sprays were more than likely ineffective because i couldnt put them as far spread as i needed to due to having pets and asthma the bug bombs require multiple applications as well as many days to clear before reentering the house and i never had a chance to be out of the house for more than a week i made a huge mistake of taking furniture with me when i moved out of my parents house so naturally the little pests came with me i considered tenting the house and everyone always told me that gels are uselessafter a year and a half of trying spray after spray after bomb of different chemicals that made me sick and i couldnt put in places in need of it because of my pets i figured what the heck i had originally gotten a pack of a small tube of gel and  baits of this brand the difference within a week was pretty outstanding with just the smaller tube and the baits i went from seeing probably  roaches a day to seeing maybe  and had carcasses everywhere i had only put it in the kitchen and there were still nests throughout the house seeing the difference it made with just the small tube i decided to order the bigger one and some bait strips of the same brandi put the gel anywhere i couldnt put a strip that my pets wouldnt get into and that i could avoid bumping into i put it under my sink in the cracks and crevices in the walls and window on top of the stove in an area that doesnt get hot it is flammable be careful i put some strips in the cabinet where i store spices and snacks always make sure you have every container sealed as best as possible roaches can squeeze into everything and you dont want them tracking the bait and the diseases they carry into your food i put this stuff virtually everywhere anywhere that i could and not worry about it i even put a few of the strips on my living room table and wrapped the areas in foil so the cats cant get into it i was really determined to get this in any place that roaches might crawl i highly suggest you do the samei bought this tube of the gel on may  and the other packages only a week or  before then i am sitting here on august  telling you this i have gone from seeing  roaches a day to recently  or  a week yes they still are going to be around they live within the walls you cant really get  rid of them especially if you live in a  year old house in florida like i do or something similar even expert exterminators will tell you this if theyre being honest however i have seen more than a  decrease in these little monsters since using this producti also highly recommend putting out some glue mouse traps in the ares that have the highest traffic it seems a bit weird but the glue on the traps acts as a bait because it is roaches favorite food and they cant resist it i put some out while using this product and they were filled within a couple of weeks i replaced them and theyre still catching a straggler here and there i even had times that had eggs hatch on them so that was a good  extra roaches that never got the chance to roam freei whole heartily recommend this product to anyone plagued with these demons as i have been it has saved what little sanity i have left i can sleep at night a little better now knowing theres not a swarm of roaches in my house anymore i am not someone that is trying to get you to waste your money or your time i did not receive a free product in exchange for my review i am someone that truly wants no one else to go through the hell i went through my entire life with these monsters i understand that all cases are different roaches are amazing little creatures and some have resistances to things that others dont at the end of the day you really arent spending much money to get this product and it has more good reviews than it does bad its worth at least trying and hopefully you have amazing results like i did
product: combat max roach killing gel  grams

review: the toothpaste is definitely ruined by the addition of some toxic ingredients and something else you people out there dont know so this is going to be a real eye opener i have been making as a research project a medical pdf library and have almost pdfs in the dental section of the library was cavity prevention and i made another discovery you all need to hear about did you notice another ingredient in the toms toothpaste is glycerin now this is big red flag and here is why a mother can tell you her story nextlast year i bit down hard on a peanut and broke one of my molars in half right down through the root it became abscessed and i had no choice but to have it removed other than this unfortunate event i have always had good teeth i was  years old before i had my first cavity so you can see that teeth have been a nonissue for me for a long time since i went to the dentist to have my abscessed tooth removed three months ago she found  or  cavities plus gum disease this is very disturbing since i have been very good about flossing particularly careful since i was walking around for a while with a broken tooth in my mouth i found it strange that i was doing all that i was supposed to do but my mouth was worse instead of bettersince then of course i have been researching teeth several sources said that commercial toothpaste is bad because it has glycerin in it glycerin leaves a film on your teeth this film prevents remineralization of the teeth i never heard of such a thing apparently the saliva is full of minerals and will deposit those minerals in the microscopic holes and pits in the surface of the teeth caused by sugar or whatever this remineralization is a normal process that prevents the holes from becoming bigger and then becoming cavities it did not surprise me that the body had a way of fixing teeth if allowed to do so so with that being said i stopped using toothpaste and started using baking soda to brush and  to rinse i can report to you that one of the cavities is completely gone it was in a toothnext to the one that was removed so i could see it in the mirror gone looked at the tooth justtoday the others may be healing as well but i cant see them they are on the topthis is one of those things they blame on age in fact they said that to me at the dentists office since they couldnt blame smoking or lack of oral hygiene you do all the right things but your condition is worse to that i say bull it has nothing to do with age the system is in place for teeth to repair themselves but the right things get in the way of the process then you get to spend money at the dentist to be fair i want to also report that i read the comments on black walnut tincture for tooth decay i have been using it twice a day two droppers full in a small amount of water enough to swish and then swallow this could well be what turned the tide for me in addition to the good oral hygiene noted above i will continue the black walnut this is one of my victories that came straight from the earthclinic members im posting more personal stories below that prove you teeth are designed to heal themselves even if they have cavitiesi am  and last year the dentist told me i had my first cavity  it was notgoing to heal he said it was too far advanced and not possible i told him ididnt want to deal with it because i was diagnosed with stage  carcinoidcancer and had recently had surgery to cut out a tumor the thought ofcutting something else out of my body when i was working so hard to healmy body didnt make sense to me so i found your site read your tipsmade homemade remineralizing toothpaste ate a lot of bone broth and goodbutter cut down on phytic acid etci went back to the dentist  months later and he was shocked that the cavitywas gone he wanted me to tell him everything i had done i felt so goodcatherine d from virginiaanother testimony for youeverything in your body healsi had a cavity once and the dentist was picking at it and he mubbled thats strangehe said im going to take an xray and i started sweating blood i said is there something terribly wrong he said no it seems your tooth is making a calcium barrier he made the xray and he confirmed it my tooth was reacting to a cavity and wascocooning it with calcium the dentist said that the tooth was hardening itself at the point where the cavity was and it stopped the cavity from expanding he left it and he said i should come back in  months so he could look at it again its still there the cavity but its rendered harmlessthe doc even asked if he could show my xrays to other dentists i said sure fine by me teeth are alive they are not dead little rocks in your mouth they are living structures so naturally it heals itself the problem is that our teeth are under constant attack soit has little time to heal but if you give it the time and the proper resources it will inevitably heal

review: agree the claim of less than  peanuts does not appear to be true there are certainly more peanuts in each bowl we pour outabout fortunately peanuts are extremely healthy and a good source of protein but the price should be adjusted downward for this high percentage of peanutsand what s so great about sea salt  was wondering about that is it really better  enclosed in the mayo clinics review and you can decide it seems that  may just be a marketing ploy toowhats the difference between sea salt and table saltanswers from katherine zeratsky rd ldthe most notable differences between sea salt and table salt are in their taste texture and processingsea salt is produced through evaporation of ocean water or water from saltwater lakes usually with little processing depending on the water source this leaves behind certain trace minerals and elements the minerals add flavor and color to sea salt which also comes in a variety of coarseness levelstable salt is typically mined from underground salt deposits table salt is more heavily processed to eliminate minerals and usually contains an additive to prevent clumping most table salt also has added iodine an essential nutrient that helps maintain a healthy thyroidsea salt and table salt have the same basic nutritional value despite the fact that sea salt is often promoted as being healthier sea salt and table salt contain comparable amounts of sodium by weightwhichever type of salt you enjoy do so in moderation the dietary guidelines for americans recommend limiting sodium to less than  milligrams a day  or  milligrams if youre age  or older or if you are black or if you have high blood pressure diabetes or chronic kidney disease

review: russell stover candies were always good you could count on them to be fresh and tasty at a reasonable price  i dont know what theyve done to them but over the past  years or so they changed a lot  my mom and i always used to buy a box at holidays and special occasions or any day that we wanted a piece of chocolate candy  we stopped buying them a few years ago when we noticed the decline in quality  they became much too sweet  the texture also changed  the buttercreams were my favorites and they went from being creamy smooth and delicious to thick and grainyi asked my family not to get me any chocolates like this for valentines day this year but my brother forgot and bought a box each for me and for my mom  i gave it another chance and unsurprisingly they were bad  they are like hard lumps of sugar with softer sugar fillings  i like sweets but these are so sweet that i couldnt eat more than two pieces  they dont even have the same great flavor they used to have  i tried the buttercreams and of course they were disappointing  the vanilla buttercream had little tough bits in it that had the texture of coconut which is strange  years ago it was smooth and fluffy  one of my relatives came over to visit and tried a couple of pieces  one was so sweet that she started coughing and had to take a sip of coffeeif you remember russell stover of years ago and are expecting the same you will be disappointed  if you want real chocolate candies try a local chocolatier or some brand that makes better quality candies  it is hard to find nowadays as most mass marketed chocolates are using cheap ingredients  they are not worth eating given how bad they are for you they dont taste good enough to justify eating them  sad to see another company go downhill

review: let me start by saying i have had a consistent supply of persagel  in my medicine cabinet since i was  years old  that was  years ago it has taken me years of trial and error to figure my acne out my most recent and worst ever breakout began several months ago just before my  birthday cystic pimples popped up constantly around my mouth chin upper lip and started crawling up my cheeks loads of research led me once again back to benzoyl peroxide i had a bottle of this in my cabinet and started using it  times daily this was a few days ago and there is already a significant improvement in my acne  percent of my spots have dried upi have realized that every bad breakout i have had since my teenage years has occurred when i stopped using this why did i stop using it in the first place i wanted to experiment i went through a phase where i wanted to try only natural products coconut oil tea tree oil etc boom acne most recently i stopped using it because i didnt have any spots seriously boom acne when you use so many products and have advice thrown at you from every angle the connection isnt always evident when used properly this product has consistently kept my acne under control for  yearsa few warnings  this product will bleach fabric wash your hands very well after use  this will dry your skin out until you feel like you want to scratch your face off my advice is to start by using it only once per day maximum or once every other day use it only on active spots not all over your face  this will make your skin particularly sensitive to sunlight always use spf if you plan to go out after applying the creamthe regimen that works best for me is  wash hands  wash face with gentle cleanser gently pat dry with a clean towel  allow skin to air dry for about  minutes  wash hands again  apply benzoyl peroxide cream on spots rub it in gently like a lotion  wait another  minutes to allow the cream to sink in  wash hands again  apply a generous amount of moisturizer all over face this is a must
product: clean amp clear persagel  acne medication with  benzoyl peroxide pimple spot treatment amp medicine for acne skin care  oz
